View From the Ground brought America back into the Top Ten with the exquisite "You Can Do Magic," one of the best soft rock anthems of the early '80s. It was an unexpected but welcome comeback for the group, and it seemed like they could continue to spin out hits with its sequel, 1983's Your Move. Your Move is the eleventh original studio album by American folk rock duo America, released by Capitol Records on June 3, 1983.
